0.85 w 54 709 m 558 709 l S
BT /F2 10 Tf 54 691 Td (Q: What validations are used?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 677 Td (A: Required fields, duplicate check, product name length, numeric and positive selling) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 663 Td (price.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 54 644 Td (Q: What table stores product data?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 630 Td (A: The products table stores product information.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 604 Td (Member 4 Q&A - Backup and Recovery) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 54 584 Td (Q: What is the purpose of backup and recovery?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 570 Td (A: To protect system data by saving and restoring database state.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 54 551 Td (Q: Where are backup files stored?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 537 Td (A: They are stored as .sql files in the local /backups folder.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 54 518 Td (Q: What happens during restore?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 504 Td (A: The file is validated, a safety backup is created, and SQL statements are executed into) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 490 Td (the database.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 54 471 Td (Q: Why is restore risky?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 457 Td (A: It can overwrite current database records.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 54 438 Td (Q: How are backup files validated?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 424 Td (A: The system checks .sql extension, readability, non-empty size, and SQL-like content.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 54 405 Td (Q: Why is Automatic Backup not included in the presentation module?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 391 Td (A: Because the user-facing Backup and Recovery page focuses on manual backup and restore) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 377 Td (actions. The presented implemented features are create, restore, history, download, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 363 Td (delete.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 54 344 Td (Q: What if backup fails?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 330 Td (A: The controller returns error JSON and the UI shows a failure alert.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 54 311 Td (Q: What if restore fails?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 297 Td (A: The system returns an error message and includes the safety backup filename if one was) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 283 Td (created.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 54 264 Td (Q: How do you protect backup files?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 250 Td (A: Use login protection, validated paths, and recommended server rules to prevent public) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 236 Td (access to /backups.) Tj ET
